:"ProvisioningMode"}],"title":"ProvisioningMode","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The strategy for executing a user-data script on a VM.","type":"text"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/virtualization/using-icloud-with-macos-virtual-machines":{"title":"Using iCloud with macOS virtual machines","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization\/using-icloud-with-macos-virtual-machines","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization\/using-icloud-with-macos-virtual-machines","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using iCloud with macOS virtual machines"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/jenkinsguide","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","type":"topic","title":"Configuring Jenkins Nodes","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS CI\/CD."}]}}}